Subset of Tuberculosis data

Source: R/data.R
tb_clean.Rd

See references for more details. The data is collected between 2003-2009 in Maryland, USA. This is originally from (Xie et al. 2018)

tb_clean

Format

<<<<<<< HEAD

The object is a data frame of dimension 1137x7. Each row is a detected case of TB.

sex

Sex of individual (F/M/Unknown)

county

County in Maryland of individual

race

Race of individual (Asian/Black or African American/White)

spsmear

Smear status of individual (positive/negative/unknown)

hivstatus

HIV status of individual (positive/negative/unknown)

homeless

Homelessness status of individual (yes/no)

groupr

Cluster group

rel_time

detection time relative to first individual in cluster

=======

The object is a data frame of dimension 1137x10. Each row is a detected case of TB.

sex

Sex of individual (F/M/Unknown)

county

county in MD

ageatrept

age of individual

race

race of individual (Asian/Black or African American/White)

spsmear

Smear status of individual (positive/negative/unknown)

hivstatus

HIV status of individual (positive/negative/unknown)

homeless

Homelessness status of individual (yes/no)

INIT_REGIMEN_START_DATE

date of start of treatment

PCR.Cluster

Cluster group (if any)

datecoll

Date sputum was collected

References

Xie YL, Cronin WA, Proschan M, Oatis R, Cohn S, Curry SR, Golub JE, Barry III CE, Dorman SE (2018). “Transmission of Mycobacterium tuberculosis From Patients Who Are Nucleic Acid Amplification Test Negative.” Clinical Infectious Diseases, 67(11), 1653--1659.
